The paper focuses on a software engineering problem related to dependency management in Java projects, which suggests cs.SE as the most likely category. The proposed technique involves analyzing library API usage, which could fall under cs.PL (programming languages) or cs.SD (software development). The survey conducted with Java developers could also be relevant to cs.LG (machine learning) or cs.IR (information retrieval) if the data analysis techniques used in the survey are sophisticated enough to fall under these categories.
